EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 172300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING A LARGE COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE LIES TO THE W
AND SW OF THE UK AND IRELAND WITH MULTIPLE SMALL CENTRES. AT THIS TIME THE
MAIN SMALL LOW CENTRE IS EXP 982 SOLE OR SHANNON. MEANWHILE A RIDGE EXTENDS
FM THE AZORES INTO IBERIA AND A BROAD AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE IS SITUATED ACROSS
MUCH OF CONTINENTAL EUROPE. A WEAK PRESSURE TROUGH ALSO LIES ACROSS SCANDINAVIA.
BY MIDNIGHT ON THURSDAY THE MAIN SMALL LOW CENTRE SW OF IRELAND RPDY DEEPENS
AND IS EXP JUST W OF ROCKALL 976 BEFORE MOV SLWY NWARDS AND THEN NWWARDS
FORMING A LARGER SCALE LOW CENTRE 977 ROCKALL BY MIDDAY ON FRIDAY. THE LOW
FILLS AND MOVS NE TO LIE NEAR THE NERN ISLES 989 BY SATURDAY EVENING. NO
GALES ARE EXP TO AFFECT THE CULLERCOATS REGION THROUGHOUT THE FCST PERIOD
